description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Radiographer looking for your next role? Are you looking for the next step in your career or are you looking to add extra skills to your portfolio? If you are an innovative individual who would like to support a world class service and bring your expertise and skills in radiology to the team, we would like to hear from you. We are looking for a Diagnostic Imaging Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practice Plus Group Hospital, Shepton Mallet has been rated Outstanding by the CQC, putting it at the very top of the regulator’s quality ratings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a practitioner outside of the local area we would welcome your application and there is a very generous relocation package available to support you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supported by our experienced Head of Nursing and Clinical Services, Catherine, and our Practice Plus Group Diagnostic Imaging Lead, Fiona, you will be responsible for managing the radiology department. This will include ensuring the provision of a high quality, safe and cost effective service. You will take responsibility for clinical and professional standards, staffing and governance as well as developing relationships with neighbouring acute NHS trusts and CCG’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an experienced HCPC registered Radiographer coming from the NHS or a private hospital, you will have experience of working in a supervisory or lead role. You will bring with you a broad knowledge of techniques for all radiological modalities including x-ray, theatre radiography and MRI. You will also have experience of analysing x-ray images and be able to recognise abnormalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your leadership and clinical skills will help you to provide support and encourage all staff working in the radiology department. We encourage sharing of best practice across our site to develop your skills and take advantage of our excellent clinical leadership knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Practice Plus Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In turn we will support you to help you grow in your role and take your career in the direction you want to go. We’ll help you be the best you can be. When you’re part of the Practice Plus Group team, you don’t just have a job. You have a career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything we do is focused on providing a high standard of safe and effective patient care. As a CQC Outstanding rated hospital we believe in developing and nurturing our people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our team members to feel motivated and rewarded. So we offer a competitive package of pay and benefits. We also recognise the value of a healthy work-life balance – so we always try to be flexible, helping you fit your working life around your home life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for the role click on the link below. If you have any questions contact Sonia Sanghvi in our friendly resourcing team.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will contact all shortlisted candidate but please note Practice Plus Group retain the right to remove the advert prior to the closing date if a suitable candidate is appointed. Our employment offers are subject to receipt of satisfactory pre-employment checks. At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities. Applicants must have the right to work in the EU.&lt;/p&gt;
